HEADWORD: Smokejack
<hw>Smoke"jack`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A contrivance for
turning a spit by means of a fly or wheel moved by the current of
ascending air in a chimney.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Smokeless</ent>⟦br⟧
